WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.000
ComfyUI is a tool to make creative workflows used by professionals in the media and entertainment space.

00:09.000 --> 00:15.500
Most of the tools out there right now sort of treat AI models as a black box and something where you have to learn how to prompt.

00:15.500 --> 00:19.500
We believe since the beginning that there is a better way with open source models.

00:19.500 --> 00:29.000
You can within a very graphic environment combine different models' components together for the highest level of control and quality

00:29.000 --> 00:31.500
that you can get out of generative AI.

00:31.500 --> 00:36.500
It really is the tool that's pushing the boundaries of creative work with AI.

00:36.500 --> 00:42.000
ComfyUI has the most number of models and toolkits and ultra-level of controllability.

00:42.000 --> 00:47.500
It's a tool used by Hollywood studios to create videos, advertising agencies to create images.

00:47.500 --> 00:49.500
It can be used in any creative field.

00:49.500 --> 00:55.500
One huge benefit of working at Comfy is being energized by the community around Comfy

00:55.500 --> 00:57.000
and that includes people within Comfy.

00:57.000 --> 01:02.000
So everyone is using the product and that way you can connect with the product on a deeper level.

01:02.000 --> 01:09.000
A lot of our initiatives, whether they're business initiatives or features, are driven by engineers who kind of see, you know,

01:09.000 --> 01:11.000
this is something that I think could be really valuable.

01:11.000 --> 01:17.500
So we have engineers really not just, you know, implementing the tasks they are assigned, but driving the product forward.

01:17.500 --> 01:23.000
Designing for ComfyUI is one very challenging and second super exciting.

01:23.000 --> 01:30.000
Nothing has been defined yet, so you will be at the frontier inventing new standards and patterns.

01:30.000 --> 01:32.500
Our culture has proven to be very transparent.

01:32.500 --> 01:38.500
The entire source code of this company is also open towards our employees.

01:38.500 --> 01:43.000
My goal is to make open source win.

01:43.000 --> 01:51.000
There are only a few companies who are trying to be the next generation of creative tooling,

01:51.000 --> 01:56.000
but I think we're the only one where if we win, everyone wins.

01:56.000 --> 02:00.500
We don't know what the future exactly looks like, but we are building that future.

02:00.500 --> 02:06.000
We hire really smart, hardworking people and give them the freedom to solve really difficult problems.

02:06.000 --> 02:10.000
So if that sounds like you, I think you would be very successful and happy here.
